				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Concerned about High End raiding as a bard..<a name="40028"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 14 04 5:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First off, bards don't need gear to be powerful.  Secondly, yea I suppose being uber geared lets you do more things than not.  But as a bard, any average joe can at least <i>try</i> everything and may have a chance, the gear just makes it easier.  As with a rogue, if you don't have the gear, some things may be simply impossible.
<br />

<br />
Of course this can be said for all classes, and asking to compare the difference between uber/nonuber rogues and uber/nonuber bards is like apples to oranges since what a bard can do is not based on how long he can survive in head to head combat(ala rogue).
<br />

<br />
So no, you won't be able to walk up to an equal level player and say &quot;I soloed phinny and you can't! hahaha&quot; but you may be able to do it more easily.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, the biggest difference I've found is having mana for 7 consequetive fades.  This lets me try something without having to die a lot...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
