				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Concerned about High End raiding as a bard..<a name="40078"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 15 04 12:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If question is about AAs 10 vrs. 500 it is pretty much a common thought that bards have about 250-300 aas that help and are worth getting without just being filler. 
<br />

<br />
So difference between a 250 and 500 isn't too much in same gear, but the difference between a 10 to 200 is amazing.  
<br />

<br />
Hehe only about 150 for me to go <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Notes: 
<br />
1.  If all you are wanting to do is solo it doesn't matter too much on aa or equiptment.  You can kite just about anything you can kite at 60 as you can at 65+.  The only thing that changes is that you will take a bit more time to kill mob X.  Also there is not as much room for error.  /shrug
<br />

<br />
2.  Should also consider that when grouping skill &gt;&gt;&gt; AA or equiptment (when your aa and equiptment is good enough to survive 1-2 rounds of melee with a mob).  If you can chain pull a hard, switch gears and mezz an add in 3.25 secs after you see it, and just be aware how song X could apply in situation X, you should be gtg.  You will rarely be near the group from 50-0% health a critter has.  
<br />

<br />
3.  In raiding it makes much more of a difference in AAs and equiptment compared to a dps class.   This is because you WILL get rampage, you WILL forget once in a while to turn off a song on a pull (or not realize the puller is in your group),  you WILL be required to pull on occasion (you will get hit by raid mobs), you WILL want to be able to max out your resists if doing AoE or PoV if it is resistable.   So AAs and equiptment is required to survive a lot of these situations. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
