				<td colspan="2"><span>I think we're missing the most important aspect of this question. Bards are not defined by their gear .. the differance between a really good bard and a mediocre is skill and experiance level. 
<br />
A bard that has 'earned' ( this does not include power AA hording in the elementals ) 500 aa has the experiance and practice to be more efficient. And if you have played the end game you know there is equipment that does make you just a step ahead. 
<br />
Yes is my answer to your question, my RL friend and I play bards in our guild he has almost 600 aa I'm ranging in just over 200, his gear aside.. the efficiency with which he plays is superior than someone that has only effectively accomplished 51st level 10 times to his 500+. Gear included your limitations are restricted even less. There's a smoothness of transition or roles that practice gives you. And that's all the AA points are, practice makes perfect. </span></td>
